---
target: builder
version: 1
validations:
  - name: builder-package-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/builder/builder.go
    contains:
      - "package builder"

  - name: builder-struct-defined
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type Builder struct" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: build-options-defined
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type BuildOptions struct" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: build-method-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func.*Builder.*Build" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: clean-method-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func.*Builder.*Clean" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-method-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func.*Builder.*Validate" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: builder-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: go test ./src/builder/...
    exit_code: 0

  - name: build-options-has-profile
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "ProfileName" src/builder/builder.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: builder-uses-dag
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that the builder:
      1. Uses the graph package to build a DAG from targets
      2. Uses topological sort to determine build order
      3. Respects dependencies (builds dependencies before dependents)
      4. Stops building on first failure
      5. Supports dry run mode (prints plan without executing)
      6. Uses the agent interface (not a concrete agent) for building
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/builder.go"]

  - name: builder-runs-schema-validation
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that the builder runs schema validation as Step 0 of every build and validate operation:
      1. Build() calls parser.ValidateAllSpecs before loading targets
      2. Build() calls config.ValidateConfig before proceeding
      3. If any error-severity violations are found, build aborts with clear error listing all violations
      4. Validate() also runs schema validation before running validations
      5. Schema validation errors include file paths and field names
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/builder.go"]

  - name: builder-tests-use-mock-agent
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify builder tests:
      1. Use a mock agent (not a real CLI agent)
      2. Test the full build pipeline with mock responses
      3. Test dry run mode
      4. Test force rebuild
      5. Test dependency ordering
      6. Test failure handling (agent returns error -> build stops)
      7. Test schema validation abort (malformed spec -> build doesn't start)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/*_test.go"]
---

# Builder Validations

The builder is the most complex package, integrating all others. Tests must use mocks for the agent and state manager to be fast and deterministic. The key invariants: schema validation runs first, dependency order is respected, failures halt the build, and dry run never invokes the agent.
